  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for the Linux Kernel (Live Patch 24 for SLE 15 SP1)",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for the Linux Kernel 4.12.14-197_89 fixes several issues.\n\nThe following security issues were fixed:\n\n- CVE-2020-3702: Fixed a bug which could be triggered with specifically timed and handcrafted traffic and cause internal errors in a WLAN device that lead to improper layer 2 Wi-Fi encryption with a consequent possibility of information disclosure. (bsc#1191193)\n- CVE-2021-42739: The firewire subsystem had a buffer overflow related to drivers/media/firewire/firedtv-avc.c and drivers/media/firewire/firedtv-ci.c, because avc_ca_pmt mishandled bounds checking (bsc#1184673).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
